Single hepatocellular carcinoma (phi < or = 5 cm) in liver cirrhosis. Early diagnosis and surgical removal. 721 patients with liver cirrhosis were regularly screened by sonography and determination of alpha fetoprotein during a period of eleven years (1.1.1982-1.1.1993). In 137 of them hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) was diagnosed 28 (20.4%) had a unilocular HCC with a diameter up to 5 cm. Diagnosis was regularly verified by sonographic guided puncture, in rare cases by laparoscopy and biopsy. Beside a diameter of 5 cm the tumor should be localized at least 5 mm from the main structures in the hilus, and not in the centre of the liver